240
00:13:15,539 --> 00:13:16,960
I spent three years in that position.

241
00:13:17,500 --> 00:13:21,419
But to be honest, it wasn't an area of journalism I wanted to stay in long term.

242
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:22,440
I see.

243
00:13:22,679 --> 00:13:24,759
So why did you decide to leave finally?

244
00:13:24,759 --> 00:13:28,379
I just felt that the paper couldn't offer me any new opportunities.

245
00:13:28,879 --> 00:13:31,820
I really needed a more challenging role, to be honest.

246
00:13:38,100 --> 00:13:42,820
Alright, so talking about your last employer, this is a pretty ideal thing.

247
00:13:43,340 --> 00:13:48,779
Now, do you have any advice that you can give our listeners about describing your last job?

248
00:13:48,879 --> 00:13:50,740
Why did you leave your previous employer?

249
00:13:51,220 --> 00:13:53,960
Well, I do have a little bit of basic job advice.

250
00:13:53,960 --> 00:13:57,139
I would say don't complain about your last employer.

251
00:13:57,200 --> 00:14:02,659
Don't say my boss was mean, my coworkers were lazy, my company was terrible.

252
00:14:02,759 --> 00:14:10,659
Because usually as a person doing an interview, that makes you think that this person, if they work for you, will complain about you.

253
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:14,720
And so I think it's important, like what Rebecca does in this dialogue, to keep it positive.

254
00:14:15,159 --> 00:14:18,659
Every negative situation can become a positive experience.

255
00:14:18,980 --> 00:14:22,779
So the job was tough, but it was a good challenge, right?

256
00:14:22,779 --> 00:14:26,159
Or but, she learned how to do many new things.

257
00:14:26,460 --> 00:14:26,860
Exactly.

258
00:14:27,539 --> 00:14:36,820
I think this is important for anybody in any language, but in English especially, to use some of these phrases and to say, you know, I really like a challenge, or I didn't feel this was challenging enough.

259
00:14:37,419 --> 00:14:38,019
Things like this.

260
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:43,039
As opposed to, my old boss is so mean, he made me work on the weekends.

261
00:14:43,340 --> 00:14:44,820
That company is so terrible.

262
00:14:44,960 --> 00:14:46,580
I mean, that kind of stuff no one wants to hear.

263
00:14:46,580 --> 00:14:58,240
Yeah, exactly, and I think it's not really useful because even if the company is the competitor, so you're not really getting the extra points for giving them like the dirty secrets of what was going on in the company.

264
00:14:58,379 --> 00:15:03,379
Maybe saying, oh, my coworkers, they were just so mean to me and stuff like this.

265
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:08,440
Yeah, no, it makes you seem like a complainer, and no one wants to hire a complainer.

266
00:15:08,759 --> 00:15:08,960
Exactly.

